## **W9D2 — Grammar Tip (Reactions)**
 
*Week 9 · Day 2 · Tuesday · Grammar Tip · text*
 
**🔵 prompt_text**
 
[Tip] How to react naturally when travelling! ✈️
 
When someone shares exciting news while travelling, the first second matters.
 
A warm, natural reaction tells them: "I'm listening and I care!"
 
👂 React first — then talk
 
Examples:
 
[Voice] "No way!" — can't believe it, in the best way
 
[Voice] "That's amazing!" — warm and genuinely impressed
 
[Voice] "Oh wow!" — instant, natural surprise
 
Try saying each example out loud before writing!
 
>> The secret: say "Oh" or "No way!" FIRST — before your full reaction. It buys you a second to think AND sounds so much more natural. Travel conversations move fast — this gives you a moment to catch up!
 
[Practice] Your fellow traveller at a hostel says: "I just got back from a day trip to an island — it was unbelievable!"
 
Write how you would react. Start with a reaction word!
 
**🟡 prompt_text_japanese**
 
📚 文法ポイント：旅先での自然な反応パターン
 
• No way! — 「まじで？！」驚きと興奮を同時に表す
 
• That's amazing! — 「すごい！信じられない！」（大きなニュースに）
 
• Oh wow! — 「うわ〜！」驚いたときの自然な一言
 
>> なぜ反応が大切なの？
 
旅先では初めて会う人と話すことが多いです。
 
温かい反応は「あなたの話を聞いていますよ」のサインになります。
 
反応が小さいと、興味がないように見えることがあります。
 
よくある間違い：
 
❌ "That is good." （感情が薄い）
 
✅ "No way! That's amazing!" （ずっと自然！）
 
📌 声に出して練習しましょう：
 
"No way!" → "That's amazing!" → "Oh wow!"
 
感情を込めて言うのがポイントです！
 
**🟢 sample_response**
 
No way! An island day trip — that sounds unbelievable! Which island was it?
 
