## **W11D2 — Grammar Tip (Follow-up questions)**
 
*Week 11 · Day 2 · Tuesday · Grammar Tip · text*
 
**🔵 prompt_text**
 
[Tip] Ask better follow-up questions — travel style! ✈️
 
You already know how to react — "No way! That's amazing!"
 
Now let's make those questions more specific.
 
This week: follow-up question forms for travel conversations
 
[Voice] "Where did you go?" — the first thing any traveller wants to know
 
[Voice] "What was it like?" — how did it feel / what was the experience?
 
[Voice] "Was it worth it?" — would you recommend it?
 
Examples:
 
Friend: "I just did a cooking class this morning!"
 
You: "No way! What was it like?!"
 
Friend: "I took a local bus to a village two hours away!"
 
You: "Oh wow, seriously?! Was it worth it?"
 
Friend: "I stayed at the most amazing guesthouse last week!"
 
You: "That's amazing! Where did you go?"
 
Try saying each example out loud before writing!
 
>> The formula: React first → then ask "where," "what," or "was it" to get the full story!
 
[Practice] Your fellow traveller says: "I just did a sunrise hike — I left at 4am!"
 
React and ask a follow-up question!
 
**🟡 prompt_text_japanese**
 
📚 文法ポイント（旅先でのカジュアルな質問形）：
 
• Where did you go? → 「どこへ行ったの？」
 
  → 旅の話で最初に聞くべきシンプルな質問
 
• What was it like? → 「どんな感じだった？」
 
  → 体験や感想を聞くとき
 
• Was it worth it? → 「やってみて良かった？」
 
  → おすすめかどうかを聞くとき
 
• Cooking class — 料理教室（現地料理を習うクラス）
 
• Local bus — ローカルバス（観光客向けでない、地元の路線バス）
 
• Guesthouse — ゲストハウス（小規模な宿泊施設）
 
