## **W12D2 — Grammar Tip (Follow-up questions)**
 
*Week 12 · Day 2 · Tuesday · Grammar Tip · text*
 
**🔵 prompt_text**
 
[Tip] The most useful travel question! ✈️
 
"What happened?" — three simple words that open up any travel story.
 
Use it after a traveller:
 
[Voice] Looks stressed → "Oh no! What happened?"
 
[Voice] Shares something surprising → "No way! What happened?!"
 
[Voice] Mentions something went wrong → "Seriously?! What happened exactly?"
 
You can also be more specific:
 
"How did it end up?"
 
"Did everything work out?"
 
"Are you okay?"
 
Try saying each example out loud before writing!
 
>> Why it works so well: "What happened?" shows you want the full story — not just the headline. It tells the other person: your travel experience is interesting to me!
 
[Practice] Think of a travel problem you've heard about or experienced. Write a follow-up using "What happened?" or "How did it end up?"
 
**🟡 prompt_text_japanese**
 
📚 文法ポイント：
 
• What happened? → 「何があったの？」
 
  → What（何）+ happened（起きた・過去形）
 
  → 旅先のトラブルや出来事を聞くときに万能
 
• 応用パターン：
 
  How did it end up? → 「結局どうなったの？」
 
  Did everything work out? → 「全部うまくいった？」
 
  Are you okay? → 「大丈夫？」
 
>> "How was it?" との違い：
 
「How was it?」= 全体的な感想を聞く
 
「What happened?」= 出来事の詳細を聞く
 
トラブルの話や予想外の出来事には「What happened?」がぴったりです！
 
📌 "What happened?" を今週中に実際の会話で使ってみましょう！
 
**🟢 sample_response**
 
Oh no, seriously?! What happened — did everything work out okay?
 
